UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2371
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION designating the J.C. Holbrook Memorial Highway in
2 Breathitt County.
3 WHEREAS, James Courtney "J.C." Holbrook was born on October 22, 1907; and
4 WHEREAS, in 1953, J.C. Holbrook had served as the Magistrate in Breathitt
5 County for three and a half years and was running for re-election; and
6 WHEREAS, on July 23, 1953, J.C. Holbrook stopped a man who had been staying
7 in the area and was rumored to be an escaped convict. When J.C. Holbrook approached
8 the 1947 Chevrolet, the man inside took a .22 caliber pistol from the passenger seat and
9 shot J.C. Holbrook once in the chest; and
10 WHEREAS, J.C. Holbrook returned fire and shot the man five times, killing him
11 instantly. The 1947 Chevrolet was later identified as one reported stolen from Bourbon
12 County; and
13 WHEREAS, J.C. Holbrook was rushed to the closest doctor and was tragically
14 declared dead on arrival; and
15 WHEREAS, J.C. Holbrook represents the values of service and sacrifice that
16 continue to define our Commonwealth and this great Nation;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
19 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate a portion of Kentucky
20 Route 540 in Breathitt County, from its intersection with Kentucky Route 1812 to mile
21 point 3.7, as the "J.C. Holbrook Memorial Highway" and shall, within 30 days of the
22 effective date of this Resolution, erect appropriate signage denoting this designation.
